race.comment: BOTH BOWERS ACE (6) turned in a solid run last start over 520m at Wentworth Park finishing 4th and beaten only 1.5 lengths (29.85). Returns to favourable track. Has good early speed and can overcome the tricky draw. Can atone. ZIPPING CHETTY (3) missed the frame and was safely held latest finishing 7th at Wentworth Park following on from a second place finish (29.98) there the start prior. One of the main contenders. ALLAN KEEPING (1) goes very well this trip starting 32 times for 12 wins and 11 minors. Comes off a (22.26) win last time, scoring by 5.5 lengths in a NG over 400m at Bulli. Suited here and expected to run well. ZIPPING EVANIA (8) warrants respect following a recent placing.
